fields.description:
The following was noticed in the nc logs:
{code}
2017-04-12 02:37:17  INFO | [i-0d68251c] running instance groupId=sg-c422f051 cores=1 disk=25 memory=4500 vlan=-1 net=-1 priMAC=d0:0d:0d:68:25:1c privIp=10.20.4.165 plat=linux kernel=(null) ramdisk=(null)
2017-04-12 02:37:22  INFO | [i-0d68251c] copying/cloning blob emi-65b02eb8-529b0c73 to blob AIDAAQBDZIRKRTWAVGUQE/i-0d68251c/emi-65b02eb8-529b0c73
2017-04-12 02:37:22  INFO | [i-0d68251c] copying/cloning blob prt-01185ext3-a29e9c86 to blob AIDAAQBDZIRKRTWAVGUQE/i-0d68251c/prt-01185ext3-a29e9c86
2017-04-12 02:37:24  INFO | [i-0d68251c] assigning address: [10.10.97.29]
2017-04-12 02:37:43  INFO | allocated new sensor resource i-0d68251c
2017-04-12 02:38:54 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] timed out waiting for forked process pid=46923
2017-04-12 02:38:55  INFO | [i-0d68251c] attempt 2 of 5 to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:55 ERROR | libvirt: operation failed: domain 'i-0d68251c' already exists with uuid 673ba845-fe05-594d-016f-efa107297e97 (code=9)
2017-04-12 02:38:55 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] hypervisor failed to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:56  INFO | [i-0d68251c] attempt 3 of 5 to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:56 ERROR | libvirt: operation failed: domain 'i-0d68251c' already exists with uuid 673ba845-fe05-594d-016f-efa107297e97 (code=9)
2017-04-12 02:38:56 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] hypervisor failed to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:57  INFO | [i-0d68251c] attempt 4 of 5 to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:57 ERROR | libvirt: operation failed: domain 'i-0d68251c' already exists with uuid 673ba845-fe05-594d-016f-efa107297e97 (code=9)
2017-04-12 02:38:57 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] hypervisor failed to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:58  INFO | [i-0d68251c] attempt 5 of 5 to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:38:58 ERROR | libvirt: operation failed: domain 'i-0d68251c' already exists with uuid 673ba845-fe05-594d-016f-efa107297e97 (code=9)
2017-04-12 02:38:58 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] hypervisor failed to create the instance
2017-04-12 02:39:00  INFO | [i-0d68251c] cleaning up state for instance
2017-04-12 02:39:00 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] failed to remove some artifacts in /var/lib/eucalyptus/instances/work/AIDABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP/i-0d68251c
2017-04-12 02:39:00 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] failed to remove backing directory /var/lib/eucalyptus/instances/work/AIDABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP/i-0d68251c
2017-04-12 02:42:03  INFO | [i-0d68251c] forgetting about instance
{code}

Looking at the code there is a section of code in handlers.c::startup_thread() where we try to launch an instance and the parent process waits for the status of the child process (which calls virDomainCreateLinux()):
{code}
            } else {
                // parent process - waits for the child, kills it if necessary
                try_killing = FALSE;
                if ((rc = timewait(cpid, &status, CREATE_TIMEOUT_SEC)) < 0) {
                    LOGERROR("[%s] failed to wait for forked process: %s\n", instance->instanceId, strerror(errno));
                    try_killing = TRUE;
                } else if (rc == 0) {
                    LOGERROR("[%s] timed out waiting for forked process pid=%d\n", instance->instanceId, cpid);
                    try_killing = TRUE;
                } else if (WEXITSTATUS(status) != 0) {
                    LOGERROR("[%s] hypervisor failed to create the instance\n", instance->instanceId);
                } else {
                    created = TRUE;
                }
                if (try_killing) {
                    killwait(cpid);
                }
            }
{code}

What is happening is that the child process somewhat successfully launches the instance, but does not exit within the CREATE_TIMEOUT_SEC time period (60s). So on the next 4 iterations of the retry loop, the launch fails because of a duplicate instance:
{code}
2017-04-12 02:38:58 ERROR | libvirt: operation failed: domain 'i-0d68251c' already exists with uuid 673ba845-fe05-594d-016f-efa107297e97 (code=9)
{code}

And the NC will forget about the instance and try to remove artifacts, which will fail because the instance is running:
{code}
2017-04-12 02:39:00  INFO | [i-0d68251c] cleaning up state for instance
2017-04-12 02:39:00 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] failed to remove some artifacts in /var/lib/eucalyptus/instances/work/AIDABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP/i-0d68251c
2017-04-12 02:39:00 ERROR | [i-0d68251c] failed to remove backing directory /var/lib/eucalyptus/instances/work/AIDABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP/i-0d68251c
2017-04-12 02:42:03  INFO | [i-0d68251c] forgetting about instance
{code}

And now you have a zombie instance running.

We have had issues in the past with CREATE_TIMEOUT_SEC ref: EUCA-3420. The value was bumped the current value from 15 to 60. In some environments 60 seconds might not be long enough.

Two things need to be changed:
# The CREATE_TIMEOUT_SEC needs to be a user configurable value via eucalyptus.conf and default to 60 seconds. 
# If such a timeout occurs and we loop to try to create the instance again we need to determine if the instance is running via virDomainLookupByName() and figure out the appropriate course of action. 

The "appropriate course of action" seems a bit tricky, if the domain exists does that mean it is safe to assume that it is a functioning instance? We killed off the process, but the instance could be in an undefined state if the call was killed mid-flight.

I believe the appropriate course of action is to terminate the duplicate, continue to retry the launches and clean up properly if the launch attempts fail. 

We should also probably alert the user via log messages that this launch timeout is possibly occurring because of high load and give them the appropriate message to increase the timeout value via the configuration file.

